Should be a manageable schedule, I'd guess about 50hrs/week


—————————————
Time spent each week depends on your familiarity with probability theory and mathematical maturity. 126 materialwise is harder than 170, with a lab and hw due each week (also has a final project). hw is approximately the same amount as 170 and lab/project varies.

But 50hr/week is definitely much exaggerated for these two techs added together. I would say 61b for 6-15 hr and 126 for 10-20 hr (depends on individual)
Should be a manageable schedule, I'd guess about 50hrs/week
I've taken cs61a, cs70, ee16a and am planning to take 61b next semester for sure to declare. I was wondering if it would be possible to take eecs126, workload wise, along with 61b.
history.subject: 61b + 126
